	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Those comparison screenshots aren't consistent enough for comparison. A better way to compare video quality would be to take video snapshots with a good video digitizer accepting composite and RGB (or at least S-Video). Pointing a camera at a TV adds too much distortion (brightness, Moire effects, blurryness) and variation between different photos. You'd also need to merge even and odd fields to get a representative image, otherwise you're making the artifacts more prominent than they appear on a TV.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


