	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, the 65C02 can be had new from WDC for $5. Zilog doesn't seem to put prices on their site, but I believe the Z80 in a vanilla-processor version goes for ~$7.
<br />
<br />Also, yes, the 6502 does have INY and INX (and DEY and DEX.) Amusingly, it doesn't have INC A or DEC A (though I believe the C02 adds this.)
<br />
<br />I admit, though, that it's nicer to have more general-purpose registers as the Z80 does, and the 16-bit operations are a nice bonus as well. However, the 6502 has a clear edge on the Z80 in terms of execution times. Memblers is probably right, it probably depends on what's being done and who's doing it, but my preference leans towards 6502.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


